\begin_layout Subsection
Game structure
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The round marker and round track may be used to track of the game's progress
 through the rounds.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The cost-of-business marker and cost of business chart are used to track
 the game's progress through the various train types and thus the current
 loan interest and train maintenance costs (see ).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
There are 6 phases named after the colours of the trains they correspond
 to (yellow, green, blue, brown, red, gray):
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The game starts in yellow phase with the yellow trains (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "tab:Game-Phases"

\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "sec:Game-Phases"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Gold trains are considered yellow in all regards outside of when they are
 available for purchase (see ).
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Game phases change immediately when the first train of a new type is bought
 by the government or a company, or when a player assigns a train of that
 colour to a company.
 New available stock prices for starting new companies, track tile types
 and other changes accompany some game phase changes (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "tab:Game-Phases"

\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "sec:Game-Phases"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The game consists of a fixed rotation of eight (8) rounds:
\end_layout

